1,"Either party may terminate this Agreement upon thirty (30) calendar days' written notice to the other party. In the event of termination, the Licensee shall cease all use of the Software within five (5) business days and return or destroy all copies.","TechCorp licensed DataFlow's analytics software. After 14 months, TechCorp decides to switch vendors.","What steps must TechCorp take to end the agreement, and what is the timeline?","TechCorp must provide written notice to DataFlow. After giving notice, TechCorp has 30 calendar days until termination takes effect. Within 5 business days of termination, TechCorp must stop using the software and return or destroy all copies.",simple,termination
2,"The Contractor shall not, during the term of this Agreement and for a period of twelve (12) months following its termination, directly or indirectly solicit, recruit, or hire any employee of the Client, or induce any such employee to leave the Client's employment. This restriction applies to employees with whom the Contractor had material contact during the engagement.","WebDev Solutions completed a 6-month project for RetailMax. Three months after the project ended, WebDev wants to hire a RetailMax database administrator whom the WebDev project lead worked with daily.","Is WebDev permitted to hire the RetailMax DBA? What restrictions apply?","No. WebDev is within the 12-month post-termination non-solicitation period. The DBA is an employee with whom the Contractor had material contact during the engagement. WebDev may not directly or indirectly solicit, recruit, or hire this employee until 12 months after termination.",moderate,non_solicitation
